The paper discusses computational imaging systems, which involve the use of algorithms and mathematical models to improve image quality. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses noise characteristics and reconstruction algorithms, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions specific techniques such as focal sweep and flutter shutter, which are related to graphics (cs.GR) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
